## Change 1 — F1: SignalEfficiencyRatio session isolation (BUG FIX)

Files: `research_indicators.py`, `tests/test_research_indicators.py`

What: `efficiency_ratio(rth["Close"], window=20)` was called ungrouped on the
multi-session RTH frame. `efficiency_ratio` uses `series.diff(20)`, so at the
first eligible signal bar (`SignalBarsSinceOpen == 19 == SIGNAL_MIN_BARS`) the
20-bar lookback reached one row back into the prior session, injecting the
overnight gap into both the net-move numerator and the path-length denominator.
Fixed by adding `_session_efficiency_ratio` and computing via
`groupby(session).transform(...)`, matching `_session_realized_volatility`.

Why: This is the Method-2 substrate-leak family already fixed for RealizedVol /
AutoCorr / VarRatio / Kyle. efficiency_ratio was the one price-change-derived
column missed — it had no "does not reset" comment and no session-grouped caller.

Evidence: On the pre-fix artifact, 249/3585 trades (6.9%) at the boundary bar had
a contaminated value (mean 0.40 vs 0.30). Those are the SAME 249 trades where the
correctly-grouped SignalRealizedVol is NaN. After the fix they are NaN too.

Test: Added `test_efficiency_ratio_research_context_resets_at_session_boundary`
(two sessions). Verified it FAILS pre-fix (boundary bar = 1.0) and PASSES post-fix
(NaN). Single-session tests cannot catch cross-session leaks by construction.

