## Change 2 — F2: SignalADX is now session-scoped (DESIGN DECISION + implementation)

Files: `shared/indicators/trend.py`, `research_indicators.py`,
`tests/test_research_indicators.py`, strategy `README.md`

What: `SignalADX` was computed via `adx(rth, window=14)` ungrouped. `adx` uses
`high.diff()`, `low.shift(1)`, `close.shift(1)` and Wilder smoothing, none of
which reset at session boundaries. So every session open injected the overnight
gap as a huge spurious true range / directional movement, and the Wilder
recursion carried prior-session state into the in-session signal zone. Changed to
session-scoped via a new `_session_adx` caller loop (mirrors `_session_ofi_approx`
/ `_session_kyle_lambda`), so ADX is computed independently per session.

Decision rationale (this is the debatable one): The repo's entire convention is
session isolation — `session_atr`'s true range is session-grouped, and
`BarGapFromPrevious` deliberately does NOT flag the overnight boundary. ADX was
the lone TR-style calc that ingested overnight gaps. The old code carried a
comment claiming "intentionally multi-session," but (a) no spec doc backed that,
(b) a cross-session ADX computed on RTH-only bars is not a clean multi-session
trend anyway — it is RTH bars stitched with overnight gaps treated as 5-min
moves, so the "broader trend" reading was illusory, and (c) for an intraday
RTH fade, intraday trend strength is the relevant context. I judged session-scope
correct and consistent. Counter-argument for Codex to weigh: if you want a TRUE
broader/overnight trend feature, that needs ETH or daily data, not this hybrid —
so the right answer is "session-scope this one and add a separate daily-trend
column later if wanted," which is what I did.

Cost (documented honestly): session-scoped ADX is NaN until its ~2x14 warmup is
satisfied within the session, so early-session signals now get NaN SignalADX
instead of a contaminated value. NaN beats contaminated for slicing.

Also updated the `adx` docstring/comment in trend.py from "intentionally
multi-session" to "pure math, does not reset; caller scopes by session"
(matching the realized_volatility convention), and changed the README research
question from "broader trend strength" to "intraday (session-scoped) trend
strength."

Test: Added `test_adx_research_context_resets_at_session_boundary` (two 40-bar
sessions). Verified it FAILS on the old ungrouped code (session-2 ADX changes
when session-1 is mutated) and PASSES with session scoping.

