## Change 3 — minor: canonical Wilder DM tie-break in `adx`

File: `shared/indicators/trend.py`

What: `minus_dm` used `down_move >= up_move` (inclusive) while `plus_dm` used
`up_move > down_move` (strict), so an exact +DM == -DM tie was assigned to -DM.
Changed `minus_dm` to strict `>` so a tie is discarded from both (canonical
Wilder).

Why: Removes a latent asymmetry and matches Wilder's textbook definition.
Provably safe — verified the hand-calculated reference test
(`test_adx_matches_wilder_seed_reference_values`) has no +DM == -DM ties, so its
expected values are unchanged. Negligible numerically; pure consistency.

