## Change 5 — F3: document percentile-column coverage (DOC ONLY, no code change)

File: `KNOWN_LIMITATIONS.md`

What: Added a section recording that `SignalATRPctile` (~27% NaN) and
`SignalKyleLambdaPctile` (~39% NaN) are sparse early in each session because
`rolling_percentile` needs `window+1` observations stacked on the underlying
indicator's own warmup.

Why: This is NOT a bug — NaN is the honest output. I deliberately did NOT change
the percentile or window math to reduce NaN, because tuning an indicator to
increase coverage would be fitting it to the data (the exact drift this repo
guards against). The right action is to document the coverage limit so the slicer
plan treats these as lower-coverage candidates.

