## Change 6 — F5: document the R-denominator side effect of stop rounding (DOC ONLY)

Files: strategy `README.md` ("Fill And Cost Assumptions"), `KNOWN_LIMITATIONS.md`

What: Added an "acknowledged side effect" note: because stops always round toward
entry, `InitialRisk` is rounded down by up to one tick, and since R divides by
InitialRisk this inflates |R| by ~1-2% of risk (both tails).

Why: I did NOT change the rounding direction. The current direction has a
defensible fill-realism rationale, and flipping it (round stops away from entry)
would just trade one bias for another (wider risk deflates |R| and makes stops
trigger less often). The honest fix is to make the doc complete rather than imply
the rounding is R-neutral. Sub-tick magnitude, accepted for v0.

